# Objective
Refactor `bubbletea::Error` to use thiserror derive macros following the unified error pattern established in charmed_rust-ea9. This enables ergonomic error handling for TUI applications.

# Requirements

## 1. Current State Analysis
Identify existing error handling in bubbletea crate and document what needs migration.

## 2. Implement thiserror-based Error Type

```rust
use thiserror::Error;
use std::io;

/// Errors that can occur in bubbletea programs.
#[derive(Error, Debug)]
pub enum Error {
    /// I/O error during terminal operations.
    #[error("terminal io error: {0}")]
    Io(#[from] io::Error),

    /// Terminal initialization failed.
    #[error("failed to initialize terminal: {0}")]
    TerminalInit(String),

    /// Terminal restoration failed.
    #[error("failed to restore terminal: {0}")]
    TerminalRestore(String),

    /// Program execution error.
    #[error("program error: {0}")]
    Program(String),

    /// Command execution failed.
    #[error("command failed: {0}")]
    Command(#[source] Box<dyn std::error::Error + Send + Sync>),

    /// Signal handling error.
    #[error("signal error: {0}")]
    Signal(String),

    /// Screen buffer error.
    #[error("screen error: {0}")]
    Screen(String),

    /// Crossterm error for terminal control.
    #[error("crossterm error: {0}")]
    Crossterm(#[from] crossterm::ErrorKind),
}
```

## 3. Add Convenience Constructors

```rust
impl Error {
    /// Creates a terminal initialization error.
    pub fn terminal_init(msg: impl Into<String>) -> Self {
        Error::TerminalInit(msg.into())
    }

    /// Creates a program error with context.
    pub fn program(msg: impl Into<String>) -> Self {
        Error::Program(msg.into())
    }
}
