 {"id":"charmed_rust-7co","title":"Add Model trait implementations to all Bubbles components","description":"# Epic: Model Trait Implementations for Bubbles Components

## Problem Statement
The bubbles crate has 16 components but only 3 have Model trait implementations:
- spinner (2 implementations)
- viewport (1 implementation)

The remaining 13 components lack Model trait impls, meaning they cannot be used standalone in bubbletea applications. This severely limits the usability of the charmed_rust port.

## Components Needing Model Trait
1. cursor - Text cursor with blinking support
2. filepicker - File/directory browser
3. help - Keybinding help display
4. list - Scrollable item list with filtering
5. paginator - Page navigation dots/numbers
6. progress - Progress bar visualization
7. stopwatch - Elapsed time counter
8. table - Data table with rows/columns
9. textarea - Multi-line text editor
10. textinput - Single-line text input
11. timer - Countdown timer

Note: key (binding types) and runeutil (string utilities) are pure data/utility modules that don't need Model trait.

## Model Trait Requirements
Each implementation must provide:
- `init()` - Return initial command (often Cmd::none() or start animation)
- `update(msg)` - Handle messages, return updated model + command
- `view()` - Render current state to string

## Success Criteria
- [ ] All 11 interactive components have Model trait impl
- [ ] Each impl handles component-specific messages
- [ ] Each impl returns appropriate commands
- [ ] Unit tests for each Model impl
- [ ] E2E integration test with multiple components
- [ ] Documentation updated with examples

